## Codebase Patterns
- SSR markup is built as template strings in `src/html.ts`; escape all
  user-controlled text at the final HTML boundary.
- Browser tests are bundled with esbuild and run in Chromium through tapout.
- Keep shared SSR and client defaults in `src/constants.ts` so hydration
  cannot drift from server output.
- Keep progressive-enhancement fallbacks in normal document flow; custom
  element definition must not be required for content visibility.
- Keep demo-owned colors in `example/style.css`; override vendored Prism
  tokens there instead of reformatting `example/prism.css`.
- Import raw demo HTML and CSS through the `test:bundle` loaders when browser
  tests need to exercise shipped example assets.
- Run CI installs with `npm ci` so platform-specific package postinstall steps
  can materialize native binaries.
- Use `@substrate-system/tapout/axe` for bundled Axe checks; its package export
  maps the extensionless subpath correctly.
- Keep project-owned stylelint globs separate from vendored Prism output.
- Keep the 79-column checker scoped to `src`, `test`, and `example`, with
  explicit exclusions for vendored assets.
- Include repository quality checks in `npm run lint` so local linting catches
  convention regressions before commits.

